"{\"uid\": \"nzherald.co.nz-travel-french-waiters-accused-of-double-dipping-tips-in-run-up-to-paris-olympics-Q5SIFF63PZF5VM5GZHEMTFKUGM\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"It's scandalous: Parisians have accused cafes of double dipping on tourist tips.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 80, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Parisians\", \"from\": 17, \"to\": 26}, {\"ngram\": \"cafes\", \"from\": 40, \"to\": 45}, {\"ngram\": \"double dipping\", \"from\": 49, \"to\": 63}, {\"ngram\": \"tourist tips\", \"from\": 67, \"to\": 79}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Photo / Getty Images French waiters and hospitality companies have been accused of swindling tourists out of their euros, introducing a sneaky second gratuity fee.\", \"from\": 81, \"to\": 245, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Photo / Getty Images French waiters and hospitality companies\", \"from\": 81, \"to\": 142}, {\"ngram\": \"tourists\", \"from\": 174, \"to\": 182}, {\"ngram\": \"their euros\", \"from\": 190, \"to\": 201}, {\"ngram\": \"a sneaky second gratuity fee\", \"from\": 215, \"to\": 243}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tourists onParis' boulevards near the Olympic Villagehave been reporting cafes charging a tip of between 10 and 20 per cent.\", \"from\": 247, \"to\": 371, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Tourists onParis' boulevards\", \"from\": 247, \"to\": 275}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Villagehave\", \"from\": 281, \"to\": 304}, {\"ngram\": \"cafes\", \"from\": 320, \"to\": 325}, {\"ngram\": \"a tip\", \"from\": 335, \"to\": 340}, {\"ngram\": \"between 10 and 20 per cent\", \"from\": 344, \"to\": 370}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is despite a gratuityalready included in French menu prices.\", \"from\": 372, \"to\": 437, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 418, \"end\": 424, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999305776908815, \"rank\": 6.896017822550989e-05, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a gratuityalready\", \"from\": 388, \"to\": 405}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French labour lawsmean a 15 per cent tip is automatically added to service at restaurants and cafes.\", \"from\": 439, \"to\": 539, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 439, \"end\": 445, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999305776908815, \"rank\": 6.896017822550989e-05, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"lawsmean\", \"from\": 453, \"to\": 461}, {\"ngram\": \"restaurants\", \"from\": 517, \"to\": 528}, {\"ngram\": \"cafes\", \"from\": 533, \"to\": 538}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is part of the reason why France is not known for its tipping culture.\", \"from\": 540, \"to\": 615, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 571, \"end\": 577, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9996895726860655, \"rank\": 0.00016855157278237697, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 548, \"to\": 552}, {\"ngram\": \"the reason\", \"from\": 556, \"to\": 566}, {\"ngram\": \"its tipping culture\", \"from\": 595, \"to\": 614}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, it appears the 2024 Olympic Games may be changing this, with an influx of international tourists.\", \"from\": 616, \"to\": 722, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Olympic Games\", \"from\": 636, \"to\": 658}, {\"ngram\": \"an influx\", \"from\": 686, \"to\": 695}, {\"ngram\": \"international tourists\", \"from\": 699, \"to\": 721}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With 15 million tourists expected to arrive at the end of July, hospitality is expecting a healthy cut of the tourist boom.\", \"from\": 724, \"to\": 847, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"15 million tourists\", \"from\": 729, \"to\": 748}, {\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 771, \"to\": 778}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 782, \"to\": 786}, {\"ngram\": \"hospitality\", \"from\": 788, \"to\": 799}, {\"ngram\": \"a healthy cut\", \"from\": 813, \"to\": 826}, {\"ngram\": \"the tourist boom\", \"from\": 830, \"to\": 846}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Though locals have accused waiters of scamming cafe goers, who are not aware of gratuity laws.\", \"from\": 848, \"to\": 942, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"locals\", \"from\": 855, \"to\": 861}, {\"ngram\": \"waiters\", \"from\": 875, \"to\": 882}, {\"ngram\": \"cafe goers\", \"from\": 895, \"to\": 905}, {\"ngram\": \"gratuity laws\", \"from\": 928, \"to\": 941}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have been shocked in the past when I have seen waiters asking foreigners for tips.\", \"from\": 944, \"to\": 1029, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the past\", \"from\": 968, \"to\": 976}, {\"ngram\": \"waiters\", \"from\": 994, \"to\": 1001}, {\"ngram\": \"foreigners\", \"from\": 1009, \"to\": 1019}, {\"ngram\": \"tips\", \"from\": 1024, \"to\": 1028}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They were just taking advantage of them,\\\" Fran\\u00e7oise a 55-year-old Parisan toldThe Times.\", \"from\": 1030, \"to\": 1118, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"advantage\", \"from\": 1052, \"to\": 1061}, {\"ngram\": \"a 55-year-old Parisan toldThe Times\", \"from\": 1082, \"to\": 1117}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's scandalous that they are doing it to us too.\\\"\", \"from\": 1119, \"to\": 1170, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 1162, \"to\": 1164}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The termle pourboire- or \\\"drinks money\\\" - is not uncommon in France, with generous-feeling patrons choosing to leave some of their change.\", \"from\": 1172, \"to\": 1310, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1233, \"end\": 1239, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9996895726860655, \"rank\": 0.00016855157278237697, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The termle pourboire-\", \"from\": 1172, \"to\": 1193}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"drinks\", \"from\": 1197, \"to\": 1204}, {\"ngram\": \"money\", \"from\": 1205, \"to\": 1210}, {\"ngram\": \"generous-feeling patrons\", \"from\": 1246, \"to\": 1270}, {\"ngram\": \"their change\", \"from\": 1297, \"to\": 1309}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the practice of obligatory tips has infuriated locals, when presented with card readers that are adding a second helping of tips.\", \"from\": 1311, \"to\": 1449, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the practice\", \"from\": 1320, \"to\": 1332}, {\"ngram\": \"obligatory tips\", \"from\": 1336, \"to\": 1351}, {\"ngram\": \"locals\", \"from\": 1367, \"to\": 1373}, {\"ngram\": \"card readers\", \"from\": 1395, \"to\": 1407}, {\"ngram\": \"a second helping\", \"from\": 1424, \"to\": 1440}, {\"ngram\": \"tips\", \"from\": 1444, \"to\": 1448}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French broadcasterBFMTVdiscovered this was a source of Gallic outrage among the citizenry of Paris.\", \"from\": 1451, \"to\": 1550, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1544, \"end\": 1549, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999877218, \"rank\": 1.2234876569850244e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a source\", \"from\": 1494, \"to\": 1502}, {\"ngram\": \"Gallic outrage\", \"from\": 1506, \"to\": 1520}, {\"ngram\": \"the citizenry\", \"from\": 1527, \"to\": 1540}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Professor Olivier Babeau told the broadcaster that he expected the rise of mandatory extra tips was partially due to the influx of Olympic tourists.\", \"from\": 1552, \"to\": 1700, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Professor Olivier Babeau\", \"from\": 1552, \"to\": 1576}, {\"ngram\": \"the broadcaster\", \"from\": 1582, \"to\": 1597}, {\"ngram\": \"the rise\", \"from\": 1615, \"to\": 1623}, {\"ngram\": \"mandatory extra tips\", \"from\": 1627, \"to\": 1647}, {\"ngram\": \"the influx\", \"from\": 1669, \"to\": 1679}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic tourists\", \"from\": 1683, \"to\": 1699}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French have gained notoriety for being mean tippers in cultures like the United States, where gratuities are used to pay serving staff's wages.\", \"from\": 1702, \"to\": 1849, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1706, \"end\": 1712, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999305776908815, \"rank\": 6.896017822550989e-05, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1779, \"end\": 1792, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999751643050344, \"rank\": 2.4836248925688768e-05, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"notoriety\", \"from\": 1725, \"to\": 1734}, {\"ngram\": \"mean tippers\", \"from\": 1745, \"to\": 1757}, {\"ngram\": \"cultures\", \"from\": 1761, \"to\": 1769}, {\"ngram\": \"gratuities\", \"from\": 1800, \"to\": 1810}, {\"ngram\": \"serving staff's wages\", \"from\": 1827, \"to\": 1848}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Though Babeau said this may soon be changing.\", \"from\": 1850, \"to\": 1895, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Babeau\", \"from\": 1857, \"to\": 1863}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You can only think that this is a way to get the French to leave bigger tips or to get foreigners to give as much as they would in their own countries,\\\" said the professor from the University of Bordeaux.\", \"from\": 1897, \"to\": 2102, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1947, \"end\": 1953, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999305776908815, \"rank\": 6.896017822550989e-05, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a way\", \"from\": 1930, \"to\": 1935}, {\"ngram\": \"bigger tips\", \"from\": 1963, \"to\": 1974}, {\"ngram\": \"foreigners\", \"from\": 1985, \"to\": 1995}, {\"ngram\": \"their own countries\", \"from\": 2029, \"to\": 2048}, {\"ngram\": \"the professor\", \"from\": 2056, \"to\": 2069}, {\"ngram\": \"the University\", \"from\": 2075, \"to\": 2089}, {\"ngram\": \"Bordeaux\", \"from\": 2093, \"to\": 2101}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's not only customers who are disgusted by tipping as something distinctly un-French.\", \"from\": 2104, \"to\": 2191, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"customers\", \"from\": 2118, \"to\": 2127}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 2160, \"to\": 2169}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One unnamed waiter described the practice \\\"like prostitution\\\", tellingThe Timesthat having to \\\"lick the boots\\\" of patrons in the expectation of a tip was undignified.\", \"from\": 2192, \"to\": 2358, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"One unnamed waiter\", \"from\": 2192, \"to\": 2210}, {\"ngram\": \"the practice\", \"from\": 2221, \"to\": 2233}, {\"ngram\": \"prostitution\", \"from\": 2240, \"to\": 2252}, {\"ngram\": \"Timesthat\", \"from\": 2266, \"to\": 2275}, {\"ngram\": \"the boots\", \"from\": 2292, \"to\": 2301}, {\"ngram\": \"patrons\", \"from\": 2306, \"to\": 2313}, {\"ngram\": \"the expectation\", \"from\": 2317, \"to\": 2332}, {\"ngram\": \"a tip\", \"from\": 2336, \"to\": 2341}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French hospitality is one of the co